components.description: The round, golden-brown pastry of a Chinese mooncake, a traditional delicacy and lunar symbol of the Mid-Autumn Festival. Many platforms feature a design or character imprinted on the crust, and depict a slice cut out to show a brown paste with a duck egg yolk inside. Twitter displays the Chinese character for “fall/autumn” or “harvest” (Áßã) on top.

version.description:
Unicode 11.0 was released on June 5, 2018. Emojis that require new code points for release are listed on this page but for the full 2018 emoji list see Emoji 11.0.

Emoji 11.0 includes every new emoji, including variations for skin tone, gender and new emojis that don't require additional code points, such as the chess pawn or pirate flag which are not shown on this page.

apple_vendor_description: On Apple devices, the moon cake emoji is presented as a delectable, circular pastry with intricate patterns pressed into its golden-brown surface. Apple‚Äôs realistic lighting and glossy finish make the textured details pop, hinting at a rich, savory or sweet filling within. This emoji evokes the traditions of the Mid-Autumn Festival, symbolizing family reunion, prosperity, and good fortune, often shared during autumn celebrations.
